In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1⁄4 cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Trim @scallions{2}. Cut whites into 1-inch pieces; thinly slice greens. Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1}(cored and diced) into 1-inch pieces. Roughly chop @cashews{1/2%ounce}.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

In a #small bowl{}, combine chicken, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, 1⁄2 tsp salt, and @pepper{}. Toss to evenly coat.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @pineapple{4%ounce}(chopped) and juice, @umami ginger sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{1}(unit), remaining cornstarch, 1⁄4 cup water, and juice from half the lime.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and bell pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in chicken and sauce mixture. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Simmer until chicken is coated and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in 1 TBSP @butter{} and as much lime zest as you like.

Divide rice and pineapple chicken between shallow bowls in separate sections. Top with scallion greens and cashews. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.